{
  "stem": "4760.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we had to keep ourself always in-- And we have to say, we-- my mother always raised us very, very strong.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She didn't put any-- she made us work hard and everything else, and I believed that has helped.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The exercise, the being in a family where you had to work, and-- not because we needed it all the time, but we had to work, regardless, from morning to night.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think it makes you body stronger.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Dora was one of the worst camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then in 19-- in April of '45, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] suddenly-- suddenly a word came down that the-- the Russian were advancing, the American were advancing.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Going back, when the American landed in France, in 1944--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was the worst time in the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because they knew something was going to happen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They let it out on us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were mean.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Meaner and meaner.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Germans.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The SS.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had a lot of older Germans who were trying not to be so mean, but the younger generation made them do things when they didn't want to.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- we suffered.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, that rationing were cut, the-- the work was put on stronger, more and more work were put on you, because they wanted that V-2 to-- to destroy England, so that the American could not land in England and-- and come to the United-- to-- to Europe.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was very, very difficult at the time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You survived.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] In 19-- then in April of [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] '45, the-- the American were not far away from Buchenwald and Dora, so they tried to evacuate-- evacuate us again to-- to another camp.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They put us again in the boxcars and shipped us out.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
